ABSTRACT
An access point in a random access wireless network is
presented, which performs medium access control for trans-
missions from a plurality of stations to the access point using
a carrier sense multiple access protocol. The CSMA protocol
is based on the access point having a variable sensitivity
level to detecting other transmissions on a wireless channel
in order to avoid data collisions. In a dense network envi-
ronment, the sensitivity level can be reduced to avoid
detecting transmissions to other access points, and thus
improve area efficiency.
